@node "mainw" "Main window"


 @{u}Main StreAmi window@{uu}


 ---------------------------------------------
 | --------------------------Info----------- |
 | |             |@{fg shine}Name:@{fg text}                    | |
 | |   StreAmi   |@{fg shine}Location:@{fg text}                | |
 | |    Logo     |@{fg shine}URL:@{fg text}                     | |
 | |             |@{fg shine}Genre:@{fg text}                   | |
 | |             |@{fg shine}MPEG Info:@{fg text}               | |
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 | --------------------Server--------------- |
 | | @{fg shine}Your Server Name@{fg text}                    |@{fg shine}B@{fg text}| |
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 | | @{fg shine}Status Window@{fg text}       | @{fg shine}Connect@{fg text} | @{fg shine}Prefs@{fg text} | |
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 ---------------------------------------------


 @{fg shine}Name:@{fg text}             The real name of the server you are connected to.

 @{fg shine}Location:@{fg text}         Where in the world is the server located!?

 @{fg shine}URL:@{fg text}              Use this URL with your browser to get more Information
                   about the server... like playlists, faster servers aso.

 @{fg shine}Genre:@{fg text}            What kind of music plays the server? Like Rock, Pop, Techno, Trance etc.

 @{fg shine}MPEG Info:@{fg text}        Shows info about the MPEG format of the stream you are listening to.
                   Like kbps/s, khz and Mono or Stereo
                   More kbps/s and khz give better sound but the stream gets much bigger
                   and you need a faster internet connection.

 @{fg shine}Your Server Name:@{fg text} The name of the server you gave it in the @{"Server list" link "serverw"}.

 @{fg shine}B:@{fg text}                Push this button to choose another server from your server list.

 @{fg shine}Status Window:@{fg text}    Gives you information about the status of StreAmi.
                   -Boring                : StreAmi isn`t doing anything
                   -Connecting            : Trying to connect to a server
                   -Connected & PreLoading: Connected and filling the NetBuffer
                   -Connected & Playing   : Connected and playing funky music
                   -Connection Timed Out  : Server may be down or VERY slow connection
                   -Server Full           : Bad luck, server is full... try again later
                   -Connection Refused    : Server down or wrong port
                   -Server unavailable    : Server down
                   -Disconnecting         : StreAmi trys to disconnect, could take a while
                   -Other?

 @{fg shine}Connect:@{fg text}          Push this button to connect to the selected server in the server field

 @{fg shine}Prefs:@{fg text}            Push this button to open the @{"Prefs window" link "prefsw"}.

@endnode

@node "serverw" "Server window"


 @{u}StreAmi Server List@{uu}


 ---------------------------------------------
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 | |@{fg shine}Name@{fg text}              | @{fg shine}URL@{fg text}       | @{fg shine}Port@{fg text}   | |
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 | |Blablabla         | 0.0.0.0   | 0000   | |
 | |                  |           |        | |
 | |                  |           |        | |
 | |                  |           |        | |
 | ----------------------------------------- |
 |      --------      --------      -------- |
 | @{fg shine}Name@{fg text} |      | @{fg shine}Host@{fg text} |      | @{fg shine}Port@{fg text} |      | |
 |      --------      --------      -------- |
 | ------------------- --------------------- |
 | |       @{fg shine}Add@{fg text}       | |      @{fg shine}Delete@{fg text}       | |
 | ------------------- --------------------- |
 ---------------------------------------------


 @{fg shine}Name:@{fg text}   The names of all servers in your list are listed below

 @{fg shine}URL:@{fg text}    The URL`s or IP`s of the servers are listed below

 @{fg shine}Port:@{fg text}   The ports of your servers are listed below

 @{fg shine}Name:@{fg text}   Enter the name of the server in the field behind

 @{fg shine}Host:@{fg text}   Enter the URL or IP of the server in the field behind

 @{fg shine}Port:@{fg text}   Enter the port of the server in the field behind

 @{fg shine}Add:@{fg text}    Push this button to add the data in the fields above to your server list

 @{fg shine}Delete:@{fg text} Deletes the selected serverentry

@endnode

@node "prefsw" "Prefs window"


 @{u}StreAmi prefs@{uu}


 ------------------------------------
 |                ----------------- |
 | @{fg shine}Audio quality:@{fg text} |high/medium/low| |
 |                ================= |
 | @{fg shine}Freq Div:@{fg text}      | 1  /  2  /  4 | |
 |                -------------==== |
 | @{fg shine}Force Mono:@{fg text}                 |  | |
 |                -------------==== |
 | @{fg shine}AHI Unit:@{fg text}      | 0 / 1 / 2 / 3 | |
 |                ---------======== |
 | @{fg shine}Audio buffer size (Kb):@{fg text} | 4-16 | |
 |                       --======== |
 | @{fg shine}Net buffer size (Kb):@{fg text} | 8 - 32 | |
 | -------------------------------- |
 | | @{fg shine}Save & Use@{fg text}| | @{fg shine}Use@{fg text} | | @{fg shine}Cancel@{fg text} | |
 ------------------------------------


 @{fg shine}Audio quality:@{fg text}          Choose playback quality of the MPEG stream.
                         There are High, Medium and Low.
                         Should only be used on slow systems and since the most
                         audio streams give poor quality anyway...

 @{fg shine}Freq Div:@{fg text}               Devides the streaming frequency through the choosed number.
                         Must not be used since most audio streams have low freq anyway.

 @{fg shine}Force Mono:@{fg text}             Play`s audio as mono only... gives extra speed but many streams
                         use mono anyway.
                         For all above have a look at the "MPEG Info" in the @{"Main window" link "mainw"}.

 @{fg shine}AHI Unit:@{fg text}               Choose the AHI unit for audio playback.
                         You can set the parameters for the units with the AHI Prefs program.

 @{fg shine}Audio buffer size (Kb):@{fg text} Set`s the size of how many audio data is send to AHI every time.

 @{fg shine}Net buffer size (Kb):@{fg text}   Set`s the size of how many data is fetched from the network.
                         (data is fetched in asynchronous way)

 @{fg shine}Save & Use:@{fg text}             Save`s all changes of the prefs and use`s them.

 @{fg shine}Use:@{fg text}                    Only use the prefs... nothing is written to the prefs file

 @{fg shine}Cancel:@{fg text}                 Forget all changes you did to the prefs


 NOTE: Prefs and server lists are stored in progdir: in a text file.
       Do not mess with it unless you know exactly what are you doing.
       You have been warned.

       Changing prefs on fly does not work. Only audio buffer size
       and net io size is updated. Save prefs and restart StreAmi to use changes.

@endnode

